phasing_duration_help: Restricts the phasing period of the transactions issued by the account. Useful in case the controlled account is compromised. The maximum duration determines for how long an attacker will be able to lock the account funds before the controlling entities are able to rescue them to a new account. The minimum duration, together with the Maximum Pending Fees, determines at what rate an attacker will be able to burn through fees the coins owned by the controlled account
maximum_pending_fees_help: Maximum sum of the pending transactions fees. Divide this by the minimum phasing duration, and you will get the amount of coins that can be spent in fees by the controlled account per block

bundler_fee_limit_help: Total amount of ARDR to be payed by this bundler
bundler_min_rate_help: The rate at which the bundler will buy child chain tokens with ARDR. The bundler will ignore transactions whose fee in child chain tokens is less than the minimum fee in ARDR which the bundler must pay for the transaction, multiplied by this rate
bundler_fee_calculator_help: Calculates the fee in ARDR which the bundler will pay for each child chain transaction to the forger of the block.
bundler_fee_calculator_help_min_fee: With this calculator, the bundler pays minimum fee in ARDR according to the current protocol rules. Any additional child chain tokens collected from the transaction remain as profit to the bundler.
bundler_fee_calculator_help_proportional: With this calculator, the bundler pays fee in ARDR proportionally to the child chain tokens collected from the transaction. Take special care to set a profitable rate, or else significant loses may occur.
bundler_overpay_help: Amount of ARDR to be additionally payed for each bundled transaction. The calculated fee by the fee calculator is multiplied by this value and the result is added to the calculated fee. Custom calculators may disregard this value.
bundler_filters_help: Set of filters for child chain transactions. The transaction is bundled only if it satisfies all filters. If one or more filters are set, this bundling rule is considered private and it's rate is not announced.
bundler_filter_help_personalbundler: Only bundle the transactions of the bundler account
bundler_filter_help_propertybundler: Only bundle transactions sent by accounts which have the "bundling" property set on them by the bundler account
bundler_filter_help_assetbundler: Bundles only transactions for asset with ID provided as parameter
bundler_filter_help_currencybundler: Bundles only transactions for MS currency with ID provided as parameter
bundler_filter_help_purchasebundler: Bundles only purchases of digital goods sold by an account provided as parameter
bundler_filter_help_quotabundler: Bundles transaction until the quota per account and transaction type is reached. The quota is provided as parameter.
bundler_filter_help_transactiontypebundl: Bundles only transaction types provided as parameter. The parameter must be comma separated string, which contains <type>:<subtype> pairs specifying the "type" and "subtype" identifier of the whitelisted transaction types. The "type" and "subtype" identifiers can be found in the transactionSubTypes field of the getConstants result.
